parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation or failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
Spare tire failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
Tire inflation or pressure issues can cause tire failure, loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
Tire recall or replacement issues can cause tire failure, loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially in rainy or snowy conditions, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers operate intermittently or not at all
wipers leave streaks or residue on the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear windshield wiper can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially in rainy or snowy conditions, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Rear windshield wiper operates intermittently or not at all
wiper leaves streaks or residue on the rear windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the windshield wipers to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility while driving, especially in rainy or snowy conditions, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers operate intermittently or not at all
smoke rises from the top of the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden cracking or shattering of the windshield can cause accidents, injuries, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: pieces of glass are scattered everywhere
powder burns or small cuts may occur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defroster/defogger system can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially in cold or humid conditions, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: windshield fogs up or ices over
plastic vent inside the heater control assembly breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal bracket can cause the pedal to fall off, leading to a loss of acceleration control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels loose or falls off
the pedal bracket breaks off from the firewall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle speed control deactivation switch can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the accelerator pedal sticks or feels stuck
the cruise control does not disengage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cruise control system can catch fire, leading to vehicle damage or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled vehicles can lead to continued risk of accidents or injuries due to the underlying defects.
symptoms: The dealer does not have the necessary parts to repair the vehicle
the vehicle is not repaired despite multiple attempts to schedule a repair.
